reviews.text: Had dinner with my friend here. Menu is perfect. Love their signature dish mussels.Service was awesome.The staff were very accommodating and friendly. Will be back definitely! Kudos to the management for having well trained people.

Casual place Bistro style with staff primarily from the Philippines. Very friendly and service minded. Great place for socializing with friends. In case you are looking for a healthy meal this might not be the best place.
Very cozy bar / restaurant. Amazing wine selection. Must try

1st visit. Left with bad impression.

Just to chat with friends over non-alcoholic drinks. So no way we got drunk. 

The place was not busy during our stay - Happy Hours. Yet we left at a rush, and I only found out at home they 'forgot' to delete an order they ran out of supply.

So if you still insist to try, remember to check the bill twice, item by item. 

Seen from inside or outside the layout is a 100% bar, weird it's positioned as a dining place...

There for lunch.  A bit pricy me around HK$200 per head but something within the price range in this area.
Food quality is flavorsome.  Chicken fillet is tender and not too dry.  The fries that come with the steak is fresh and crispy.  
Ambience is relaxing and spacious. 
I believe it is a good place for cocktail too.
